11/2/98
  Debugging the combined code.
  Trying to fix the temporal reference adjustment.

11/3/98
  Temporal reference adjustment study:
      tr_base_old + tr_old = tr_base_new + tr_new
      tr_adj = tr_new - tr_old
             = tr_base_old - tr_base_new

  For exit B pictures in the live stream, tr_base_old is the original tr_base.
  tr_base_new is the last anchor frame before exit point + 1 (where GOP header
  is inserted).
      tr_adj = tr_base - new_tr_base

  For pictures in the stored stream at entry point, tr_base_old is the splice
  point.
      tr_adj = splice_point - new_tr_base

  Temporal reference problem fixed.  

  Generalized DPI worked!  Can switch from one hits channel to another.
  Implemented TR mapping.

